- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses procedures for analyzing and describing the behavior of systems, which is a common concern in programming language design and implementation.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with well-structured transition systems, which are a type of automata used to model infinite-state systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the properties and behavior of well-structured transition systems, which can be seen as a type of data structure.
- cs.LT (Learning Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses procedures for analyzing and characterizing the behavior of systems, which can be seen as a type of learning or inference problem.
